com.ipt.ebsa.util.collection

Class PlaceholderMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ipt.ebsa.util.collection.PlaceholderMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>

    public class PlaceholderMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>, java.lang.Cloneable
    This is a normal map, but put and putAll parse the given value/values for ${parameter} and look for key "parameter" and replace ${parameter} with the value for key ${parameter}. This is done recursively, an exception is thrown if there is a loop in the recursion. You can escape $ with \$ (so in a java string "not a \\${placeholder}")
